(1) To Create input file:
	(a) install gdis
		sudo apt-get install gdis
		
	(b) Download Ag.cif from matreials project
	(c) Open Ag.cif with gdis
		gdis Ag.cif
	(d) Save as Ag.fdf
	
	
(2) To install ATOM which helps to generate pseudo potential files:

	(a) Go to Pseudo Directory in Siesta location
	(b) Download ATOM from siesta site
		wget https://siesta-project.org/SIESTA_MATERIAL/Pseudos/Code/atom-4.2.7-100.tgz
	(c) Unzip the folder
		tar xvf atom-4.2.7-100.tgz 
	(d) Go to atom folder
		cd atom-4.2.7-100/
	(e) open installation manual
		gedit 000_INSTALL 
	(f) Download and install libgridxc :
		wget https://launchpad.net/libgridxc/trunk/0.8/+download/libgridxc-0.8.5.tgz
		tar xvf libgridxc-0.8.5.tgz 
		cd libgridxc-0.8.5/
	# Follow instruction in INSTALL file
		mkdir Gfortran
		cd Gfortran
		cp ../extra/fortran.mk .
		sh ../src/config.sh
		make clean
		make
		cd ../../
	(g) Coming back to atom folder, install xmlf90 :
		wget https://launchpad.net/xmlf90/trunk/1.5/+download/xmlf90-1.5.4.tar.gz
		tar xvf xmlf90-1.5.4.tar.gz
		cd xmlf90-1.5.4
	# Follow instructions in INSTALL file
		./configure
		make
		sudo make install 
		cd ../
	(h) Come back to atom file and continue installing atom.
		cp arch.make.sample arch.make
		gedit arch.make
	# edit the path for files make following changes in the arch.make:
		XMLF90_ROOT=/home/vincent/Downloads/siesta-4.1.5/Pseudo/atom-4.2.7-100/xmlf90-1.5.4/config/data
		GRIDXC_ROOT=/home/vincent/Downloads/siesta-4.1.5/Pseudo/atom-4.2.7-100/libgridxc-0.8.5/Gfortran
		include $(XMLF90_ROOT)/xmlf90.mk
		include $(GRIDXC_ROOT)/gridxc.mk
	# Continue in the atom folder:
		make
	ATOM installed.
	
(3) Generating Pseudo potential Files with ATOM:

	cd ~/Downloads/siesta-4.1.5/Pseudo/atom-4.2.7-100/Tutorial/PS_Generation
			
	.	.	.	.
	
	.	.	.	.
	
	.	.	.	.
	
